      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your intuition about the consistency is understandable, but current smart home technology lacks the ability to detect internal emotions or micro-pauses in speech that could indicate stress. Companies would need highly invasive, cost-prohibitive biometric sensors far beyond standard thermostats to implement such tracking. The most plausible explanation is that the devices are reacting to physical manifestations of your stress, like unintentional changes in your voice or body language, rather than truly \"reading\" your mind.",
